Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createNetGroup(25.10)                                    createNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       createNetGroup - Creates an empty net group

Syntax
       createNetGroup

       [-help]

       [-mixed_signal]

       [-spacing  <minSpaceInTracks>]

       [ {[-optimizeOrder ]} | -spreadPin | -compact_area ]

       [-excludePin    {allLayer    |    sameLayer   |   allLayerInGuidedArea}
       [-keep_out_spacing <integer>]]

       { [<netGroupName> [-net <netNameList>]]}

       Creates an empty net group. A net group  can  contain  net  names,  bus
       names,  or  segments  of a bus. To add nets into the net group, use the
       addNetToNetGroup command. You can use this command after importing  the
       design.

       Note:  If a net is part of a net group, and you add the same net to an-
       other net group, the Innovus software will display a warning,  but  the
       net  will  be  added to the second net group too. However, when pin as-
       signment is performed, the net is considered part only of the first net
       group to which it was added - and not part of any other  net  group  to
       which it was subsequently added.

Parameters
       -compact_area
              Specifies  that pins in the group are assigned tightly together.
              By default, pins which are part of a group and associated  to  a
              guide can be spread inside the guide based on the area available
              and  alignment  to  targets. The compact_area option, when used,
              ignores the alignment and available area and forces the pins  to
              the  minimum  area  on  guide  honoring the minimum spacing con-
              straint and overlooking any alignment to targets.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -excludePin {allLayer | sameLayer | allLayerInGuidedArea}
              Specifies that pins in the group exclude  foreign  pins  on  all
              layers, same layer, or on all layers in the guided area.

              * allLayer:  Specifies  that  pins  in the group exclude foreign
                pins between grouped pins on all layers.

              * sameLayer: Specifies that pins in the  group  exclude  foreign
                pins grouped pins on all same layer.

              * allLayerInGuidedArea: Specifies that pins in the group exclude
                foreign  pins  in the guide area defined for the group, on all
                layers.

               Note: If guide is not defined for a group down the  flow,  all-
              LayerInGuidedArea option would be treated like -excludePin {all-
              Layer} for the group without guides behavior.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each createNetGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man createNetGroup.

       -keep_out_spacing <integer>
              Specifies the minimum spacing between the pins placed outside of
              the group, in number of tracks or pitch.

              Minimum: 0

              Maximum: 65535

              Data_type: int, optional

       -mixed_signal
              Specifies to identify a mixed signal group.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -net <netNameList>
              Specifies the name of the net(s). You  can  use  wildcards  (*?)
              with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <netGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the created net group name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -optimizeOrder
              Specifies  that pins in the group are reordered to optimize wire
              length. If this option is not selected, the pin order is exactly
              as specified in the pin group.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -spacing <minSpaceInTracks>
              Specifies the minimum spacing between the pins of the net group.

              Default: The default value is two tracks.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -spreadPin
              Specifies that pins in the group must be distributed evenly.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command creates a net group bundle1:

                createNetGroup bundle1

              * The following command creates a net group bundle1  and  allows
                re-ordering of the nets definition inside the group:

                createNetGroup bundle1 -optimizeOrder

